        },
        {
          "id": "7f1e42ae4f92_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "de5f",
          "text": "",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": {
            "mediaResource": {
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l7L3ZtCSKKs"
            }
          },
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IFRAME"
        },
        {
          "id": "7f1e42ae4f92_15",
          "href": null,
          "name": "936f",
          "text": "If you want to dive deeper into this have a look at the documentary (80mins) ‘The Money Fix’ which includes interviews with some of the world’s foremost pioneers in the field of re-designing and reforming our monetary system. It offers a history and analysis of our current money system and the design flaws of this system that underlie many of the converging crises humanity faces today. The last third of the documentary explains how alternative local and regional currencies can work to strengthen regional economies and what they have to offer in the redesign or our monetary system.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 91,
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TwmM5Nb6hiE",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 78,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "7f1e42ae4f92_16",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ba5f",
          "text": "",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": {
            "mediaResource": {
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TwmM5Nb6hiE"
            }
          },
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IFRAME"
        },
        {
          "id": "7f1e42ae4f92_17",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3d53",
          "text": "Since the bank-accepted debt that issued the money into circulation has to be paid back with interest, when the loan is paid back and the initial money created is cancelled, the cumulative interest generated remains in the system and generates a ‘debt imperative’ (having to make new loans in order to ensure sufficient money supply to service existing loans), which in turn generated a dysfunctional system that needs to keep growing in oder to avoid collapse.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "7f1e42ae4f92_18",
          "href": null,
          "name": "aa99",
          "text": "“The economic growth imperative that results in superfluous economic output and its attendant depletion of physical resources, despoliation of the environment, increasing disparities in income and wealth distribution and many other problems that plague modern civilization.”",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "PQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "7f1e42ae4f92_19",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3a10",
          "text": "— Greco, Thomas H Jr., 2015",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
